iIf software solutions can't resolve this issue, hardware can step in.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iModern motherboards typically include built-in hardware random number		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
igenerators (HRNGs), which generate random numbers using electrical		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
isignals from the motherboard. Due to the high volume of data traffic,		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ithese electrical signals are generally unpredictable, making		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ihardware-generated random numbers considered secure.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
